body:
ifdef with same conditions need to be fused.  This is similar to alwaysFusion logic, https://github.com/llvm/circt/pull/544, but the cases we need to handle are different.
We need to discuss which cases are legal. Here are some of the conditions we need to consider.

Case 1: Two consecutive ifdefs with same condition should be fused.
```mlir
rtl.module  @test1(%arg0: i1, %arg1: i1) {
  sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
    sv.fwrite "Yes"
  }
  sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
    sv.fwrite "RTE"
  }
  rtl.output
}
```
Case 2: 
Consecutive ifdefs with same condition within an always block should be fused
Note that the always block is an SSACFG region. (Current alwaysFusion logic cannot handle this.)
```mlir
rtl.module  @test1(%arg0: i1, %arg1: i1) {
  sv.always posedge  %arg0 {
    sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
      sv.fwrite "Yes"
    }
    sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
      sv.fwrite "RTE"
    }
  }
  rtl.output
}
```
Case 3:
Nested ifdefs with same condition can be removed. (Current alwaysFusion logic cannot handle this.)
```mlir
rtl.module  @test1(%arg0: i1, %arg1: i1) {
  sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
    sv.fwrite "Yes"
    sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
      sv.fwrite "RTE"
    }
  }
  rtl.output
}
```
Case 4: 
ifdef within a different condition should not be fused. 

```mlir
rtl.module  @test1(%arg0: i1, %arg1: i1) {
  sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
    sv.fwrite "Yes"
  }
  sv.ifdef "RANDOM"  {
    sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
      sv.fwrite "NO"
    }
  }
  rtl.output
}
```

Case 5:
Non-consecutive ifdefs with same condition can be fused. (Current alwaysFusion logic can handle this.)
```mlir
rtl.module  @test1(%arg0: i1, %arg1: i1) {
  sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
    sv.fwrite "Yes"
  }
  sv.ifdef "RANDOM"  {
    sv.fwrite "RANDOM"
  }
  sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
    sv.fwrite "NO"
  }
  rtl.output
}     
```
Case 6:
Same as above, Since these are SSA values, it is legal to fuse the following ifdefs  with same condition. After fusion, the values need to be renamed. (Current alwaysFusion logic can handle this.)
```mlir
rtl.module  @test1(%arg0: i1, %arg1: i1) {
  %0 = sv.textual_value "PRINTF_COND_" : i1
  sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
    %1 = comb.and %arg0, %arg1 : i1
  }
  sv.ifdef "RANDOM"  {
    %1 = comb.add %0, %arg1 : i1
  }
  sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
    %1 = comb.xor %0, %arg1 : i1
  }
  rtl.output
}
```
Case 7:
 ifdefs within a cfg region, with no side effecting operations 
```mlir
rtl.module  @test1(%arg0: i1, %arg1: i1) {
  sv.always posedge  %arg0 {
  sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
      %0 = comb.and %arg0, %arg1 : i1
    }
    %0 = comb.and %arg0, %arg1 : i1
    sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
      %1 = comb.xor %arg0, %arg1 : i1
    }
  }
  rtl.output
}
```
Case 8: 
ifdefs within a cfg region with side effect operations
```mlir
rtl.module  @test1(%arg0: i1, %arg1: i1) {
  sv.always posedge  %arg0 {
    sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
      %0 = comb.and %arg0, %arg1 : i1
    }
    sv.fwrite "SYNTHESIS = 1" // Side effecting operation
    sv.ifdef "!SYNTHESIS"  {
      %1 = comb.xor %arg0, %arg1 : i1
    }
  }
  rtl.output
}
```
